Package game

Class Cavern

  • java.lang.Object
    • game.Cavern
  • public class Cavern
extends java.lang.Object
    An instance represents a Cavern that the explorer can navigate through. The cavern is set up as a grid of Tile objects with a weighted graph of all non-floor tiles. There is an entrance to the cavern and a target location (which may also be the entrance).

    • Method Detail

      • digExploreCavern

        public static Cavern digExploreCavern​(int rows,
                                      int cols,
                                      java.util.Random rand)
        Return a new random Cavern of size (rows, cols) with no gold. All edges have weight 1, and an orb is a reasonable distance from the exit. Use rand as a source of randomness for the cavern generation.

      • digEscapeCavern

        public static Cavern digEscapeCavern​(int rows,
                                     int cols,
                                     int currentRow,
                                     int currentCol,
                                     java.util.Random rand)
        Return a new random Cavern of size (rows, cols) with random gold and edge weights. It is guaranteed that (currentRow, currentCol}) will be an open floor cell. Use rand as a source of randomness for the cavern generation.

      • deserialize

        public static Cavern deserialize​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> nodeStrList)
        Convert nodeStrList into a Cavern and return it. Precondition: The list of strings is of the format output by serialize().
